hands_on_practices.problem:
A three-dimensional finite-difference time-domain (FDTD) scheme with leapfrog time staggering is used on a standard Yee grid. Electric field components $E_x$, $E_y$, and $E_z$ are located at edge-centered positions $E_x(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j,k)$, $E_y(i,j+\tfrac{1}{2},k)$, and $E_z(i,j,k+\tfrac{1}{2})$, respectively, all at integer times $t^n$. Magnetic field components $H_x$, $H_y$, and $H_z$ are located at face-centered positions $H_x(i,j+\tfrac{1}{2},k+\tfrac{1}{2})$, $H_y(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j,k+\tfrac{1}{2})$, and $H_z(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j+\tfrac{1}{2},k)$, respectively, all at half-integer times $t^{n+\tfrac{1}{2}}$. The update of $E_x(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j,k)$ from time $t^n$ to $t^{n+1}$ uses the magnetic field at time $t^{n+\tfrac{1}{2}}$ through the $x$-component of the curl of $H$, consistent with the Ampère-Maxwell law in linear media and the Right-Hand Rule (RHR) orientation for the surface normal along $+\hat{\mathbf{x}}$. Assume a uniform grid with spacings $\Delta y$ and $\Delta z$ in the $y$ and $z$ directions and no magnetic sources. Select the option that correctly lists the exact neighboring $H_y$ and $H_z$ samples (including their indices and time staggering) that enter the discrete curl term used to update $E_x(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j,k)$ at time $t^{n+1}$, together with the correct algebraic signs mandated by the RHR about the $+\hat{\mathbf{x}}$-normal.

A. The discrete curl contribution at $(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j,k)$ is
$$
\frac{H_z^{\,n+\tfrac{1}{2}}(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j+\tfrac{1}{2},k)-H_z^{\,n+\tfrac{1}{2}}(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j-\tfrac{1}{2},k)}{\Delta y}
\;-\;
\frac{H_y^{\,n+\tfrac{1}{2}}(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j,k+\tfrac{1}{2})-H_y^{\,n+\tfrac{1}{2}}(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j,k-\tfrac{1}{2})}{\Delta z}\,.
$$

B. The discrete curl contribution at $(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j,k)$ is
$$
\frac{H_y^{\,n+\tfrac{1}{2}}(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j+\tfrac{1}{2},k)-H_y^{\,n+\tfrac{1}{2}}(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j-\tfrac{1}{2},k)}{\Delta y}
\;-\;
\frac{H_z^{\,n+\tfrac{1}{2}}(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j,k+\tfrac{1}{2})-H_z^{\,n+\tfrac{1}{2}}(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j,k-\tfrac{1}{2})}{\Delta z}\,.
$$

C. The discrete curl contribution at $(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j,k)$ is
$$
\frac{H_z^{\,n+\tfrac{1}{2}}(i+1,j+\tfrac{1}{2},k)-H_z^{\,n+\tfrac{1}{2}}(i,j+\tfrac{1}{2},k)}{\Delta x}
\;-\;
\frac{H_y^{\,n+\tfrac{1}{2}}(i+1,j,k+\tfrac{1}{2})-H_y^{\,n+\tfrac{1}{2}}(i,j,k+\tfrac{1}{2})}{\Delta x}\,.
$$

D. The discrete curl contribution at $(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j,k)$ is
$$
\frac{H_z^{\,n+\tfrac{1}{2}}(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j-\tfrac{1}{2},k)-H_z^{\,n+\tfrac{1}{2}}(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j+\tfrac{1}{2},k)}{\Delta y}
\;+\;
\frac{H_y^{\,n+\tfrac{1}{2}}(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j,k+\tfrac{1}{2})-H_y^{\,n+\tfrac{1}{2}}(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j,k-\tfrac{1}{2})}{\Delta z}\,.
$$

In addition to selecting the correct option, your reasoning must be based on first principles: start from Maxwell’s equations and use the geometric orientation implied by the RHR about the $+\hat{\mathbf{x}}$ normal of the $y$–$z$ face intersected by $E_x(i+\tfrac{1}{2},j,k)$, explaining which edges of the Yee cell contribute and why the signs are as shown.
